<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.lvrj.com/lvrj_home/2001/Apr-25-Wed-2001/news/15953177.html">www.lvrj.com/lvrj_home/20...53177.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Has a way been found to neutralize radioactive nuclear waste that has a half-life of thousands of years? Of course not. Can anyone envision that ever happening? Of course not.&quot; he continues all knowingly. <br>
<br>
Garbage. This problem was created by ignorant environmentalists. They mistakenly believed that banning the recycling of spent nuclear fuel would lead to non-proliferation and instead they only succeeded in destroying the nuclear industry. A source of infinite clean energy which would have raised the standard of living among Americans and reduced fossil fuel burning quite dramatically. Now they complain about a problem 'they' created. According to these luddites we can't bury it which would now be the safest option. So it just sits where it is or gets passed around which is ofcourse the most unsafe option. <br>
<br>
&quot;Future generations of Americans will have a huge and potentially unmanageable problem with our nuclear waste...What we need to do is to stop making more nuclear waste. Now.&quot;<br>
<br>
